  "instruction": "Is the matrix A = [[{a}, {b}], [{c}, {d}]] invertible? Find det(A) to decide.",
  "params": {
    "a": { "type": "int", "min": -6, "max": 6 },
    "b": { "type": "int", "min": -6, "max": 6 },
    "c": { "type": "int", "min": -6, "max": 6 },
    "d": { "type": "int", "min": -6, "max": 6 }
  },
  "answer_expr": "matdet2",
  "steps": [
    "Compute det(A) = ad - bc = ({a})({d}) - ({b})({c}) = {ad} - {bc} = {answer_matdet2}.",
    "A is invertible if and only if det(A) != 0."
  ],
  "tags": ["linear-algebra", "determinant", "invertibility", "2x2"]
